The paper deals with the optimization of training and data transmission strategies for block fading MIMO systems with feedback, which is a topic closely related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of feedback also involves networked communication (cs.NI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the impact of channel estimation errors, which is a common issue in machine learning (cs.MM) and statistical learning (cs.LG).
